# Protocol surface changes

Read `docs/supported-profile.md` before editing protocol behavior.

- Don’t assume. Don’t hide confusion. Surface tradeoffs.
- Minimum code that solves the problem. Nothing speculative.
- Touch only what you must. Clean up only your own mess.
- Define success criteria. Loop until verified.
- **SSDP**: search target `urn:ses-com:device:SatIPServer:1`; `LOCATION` must use `config.PublicHost` + HTTP port.
- **M3U**: five DACH channels in `internal/channels/catalog.go`; lab catalog in `internal/lab/catalog.go`; RTSP URLs must include `src`, `freq`, `pol`, `msys`, `sr`, `pids`.
- **RTSP**: support OPTIONS, SETUP, PLAY, TEARDOWN; echo CSeq; SETUP validates tuning via `lab.Manager`; unknown service → `404`; tuner exhaustion → `503`.
- **Env scenario**: `SATIP_LAB_SCENARIO=tuner_busy` → all SETUP return `503` before lab allocation.
- **Runtime scenarios**: `GET`/`POST /api/scenario`; `no_signal` → lab rejects SETUP with `503` / `Reason: no signal`.
- **Lab API**: document all endpoints in `docs/api.md`.
- Document any new simulated behavior in `docs/supported-profile.md`, `docs/api.md`, and `AGENTS.md`.

Do not claim full EN 50585 compliance.
